# Low-Level Design Template

Use with `adp-arch-lld` when producing or updating: foundation-lld.md, module-lld-*.md, lld.md, docs/02-product/FR/fr-<nnn>/fr-<nnn>-lld.md, lld-*.drawio.

This template is intentionally comprehensive. When creating an actual LLD artifact, choose the correct artifact type, complete only applicable sections, and remove or explicitly mark sections that do not apply. Do not generate empty boilerplate.

Before generating the document, ask the user for required values that would otherwise be left as `TBC`, `unknown`, or `[placeholder]`. If a value cannot be provided yet, record it under Open questions with owner, due date, and impact; do not leave bare placeholders in reviewable sections.

Before drafting an LLD when the stack is not explicit in upstream artifacts, ask which technologies should be used or whether the user wants a general technology-stack recommendation. Capture backend, frontend, database, ORM/data-access, connection/integration style, and runtime/deployment constraints.

